{"search_data": "Himachal PradeshHP Universal Health Protection Scheme \u2013 Ayushman Bharat (PM Jan Arogya Yojana)Himachal Pradesh govt. launches Universal Health Protection Scheme to provide free treatment upto Rs. 5 lakh to all the citizens along with Mukhyamantri Chikitsa Rahat Kosh Yojana, Mukhyamantri Swasthya Dekhbhal Yojana & Telemedicine Scheme,  see details of Ayushman Bharat - PM Jan Arogya Yojana (PMJAY) in Himachal PradeshAt the launch event, CM has also inaugurated OPD / IPD, Trauma Centre of Shri Lal Bahadur Shastri government medical college, Ner Chowk, and Nursing College at Ner Chowk in Mandi district.Himachal Pradesh Universal Health Protection SchemeAyushman Bharat \u2013 PM Jan Arogya Yojana is a flagship scheme of the Modi govt. to provide health insurance coverage of Rs. 5 lakh to people from deprived sections. All those people whose name appears in the SECC 2011 list will get free insurance coverage of Rs. 5 lakh for secondary and tertiary hospitalization. Interested candidates can apply online at https://hpuhps.com/ for Universal Health Protection scheme.People can check their name in the Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana final beneficiaries list and avail free treatment at 175 registered govt. and private empanelled hospitals in the state. This scheme is to ensure the vision of \u201cHealth for All\u201d in the state. PMJAY scheme will be implemented in Himachal Pradesh in trust based mode and there is no enrollment required to avail the scheme benefits.Universal Health Protection Scheme will subsume the Rashtriya Swasthya Bima Yojana (RSBY) in the state. Moreover, all those citizens who are not covered under this scheme will get included in the Mukhyamantri Swasthya Dekhbhal Yojana in which they will get an increased assistance upto Rs. 5 lakh (previously Rs. 30,000).\u092e\u0947\u0921\u093f\u0915\u0932 \u0915\u0949\u0932\u0947\u091c \u0928\u0947\u0930\u091a\u094c\u0915 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091f\u0947\u0932\u0940\u092e\u0947\u0921\u093f\u0